The paper deals with the computational complexity of computing the strong metric dimension of a graph, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves approximation algorithms, which are often studied in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The problem of computing the strong metric dimension is closely related to graph theory and combinatorial geometry, which are covered by cs.CG and cs.DS. Finally, the paper involves the study of conjectures and hypotheses related to computational complexity, which falls under the category of computational complexity theory (cs.GT).
